    <Folder>
      <name>Intelligence Summary</name>
      <Placemark>
        <name>AI Council Assessment</name>
        <styleUrl>#intel</styleUrl>
        <description>The synthesized intelligence data reveals a military posture characterized by routine operations, training, and logistics with no immediate large-scale deployments or crisis responses. US Air Force and Navy platforms dominate tracked activity, with a notable concentration of tanker, transport, and ISR missions across the continental United States, Gulf of Mexico, Central Europe, and Mediterranean. The absence of deployed US Navy vessels in the data—aside from the in-port USNS CODY—suggests a period of stabilized naval posture, possibly reflecting maintenance cycles or a focus on non-deployed training and regional support. The lifting of the naval blockade on Iran represents a significant geopolitical shift, reducing direct US naval presence in the Strait of Hormuz while maintaining a broader deterrent posture in the Middle East. Multinational exercises in the Western Pacific, such as those en route to RIMPAC 2026, indicate ongoing allied coordination but do not reflect immediate US carrier strike group or amphibious ready group deployments. The data suggests a stable global military environment with routine surveillance, logistics, and training activities, though the lack of detailed vessel positioning beyond the USNS CODY limits visibility into broader naval operations. Regional stability appears to be prioritized, with no indications of imminent conflict escalation.</description>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>0,0,0</coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
